<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-23T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-23T15:00:00-05:00" n="998" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d998">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1247: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-23T15:00:00-05:00">December 23,
                                1947—3 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1558. Not now possible give any definite info re Blandford (Embtel 2381 Dec
                        12) and civilian advisory group pending agreement by Dept and concerned Govt
                        agencies on China aid program now being prepared for presentation Congress.
                        You may in your discretion tell Gimo matter being studied by Dept and other
                        Govt agencies but no final decision yet reached.</p>
                    <p>As regards inquiry re subject matter para 2 of Reftel Dept assumes you have
                        by now reed memo of conversation betw Sec and Amb Koo Nov 13 forwarded by
                        pouch.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>